verse.lines:
{lang-eng}I’m pressing on the upward way,
New heights I’m gaining every day;
Still praying as I’m onward bound,
“Lord, plant my feet on higher ground.”{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Lord, lift me up, and let me stand
By faith on Canaan’s tableland;
A higher plane than I have found
Lord, plant my feet on higher ground.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}My heart has no desire to stay
Where doubts arise and fears dismay;
Though some may dwell where those abound,
My prayer, my aim, is higher ground.{/lang-eng}

